<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="162" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="46" pageNumber="162" type="mainText">
Worker diagnosis. - A member of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Emery" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtilissimus">P. subtilissimus</taxonomicName>
group, and immediately distinguishable from all other acacia-associated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lund" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudomyrmex</taxonomicName>
by its small size (
<collectionCode>HW</collectionCode>
&lt;0.60), elongate head (Cl &lt;0.66), apedunculate petiole, and scarcity of standing pilosity. See Ward (1989:432) for further discussion of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="162" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="46" pageNumber="162" type="mainText">
Distribution and biology. - 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Emery" baseAuthorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtilissimus">P. subtilissimus</taxonomicName>
has been collected only in Nicaragua and Costa Rica. What little is known about its biology suggests that it is a timid, non-protective species living in the thorns of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P.Miller" authorityYear="1754" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="46" pageNumber="162" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="genus">Acacia</taxonomicName>
plants occupied by (declining?) colonies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="F. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1877" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavicornis">P. flavicornis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
